---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// SEO: Schema para Listado de Partidos (Fixture)
const fixturesSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "ItemList",
  "name": "Full FIFA World Cup 2026 Fixture",
  "description": "Complete match schedule for the 2026 World Cup, including group stages, round of 32, and the grand final.",
  "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending"
};
---

<Layout 
  title="FIFA World Cup 2026 Fixture: Full Match Schedule & Venues" 
  description="Check the definitive world cup fifa 2026 fixture. Group by group matchups, dates, Eastern Time schedules, and the complete knockout bracket."
  schema={fixturesSchema}
>
  <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black mb-8 text-blue-900 tracking-tight">
    Official FIFA World Cup 2026 Fixture: All Matches and Times
  </h1>
  
  <article class="prose lg:prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
    <p>
      Following the official draw, FIFA has released the comprehensive <strong>fifa world cup 2026 fixture</strong>. Below, you will find every match organized by group, including venues, dates, and kickoff times (all times correspond to U.S. Eastern Time unless otherwise noted).
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-6 border-b-2 border-blue-100 pb-2">Group Stage Matchups</h2>
    
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-4">Group A</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li><strong>June 11:</strong> Mexico vs. South Africa – 3 p.m. (Mexico City)</li>
          <li><strong>June 11:</strong> South Korea vs. Playoff Winner – 10 p.m. (Guadalajara)</li>
          <li><strong>June 18:</strong> Playoff Winner vs. South Africa – 12 p.m. (Atlanta)</li>
          <li><strong>June 18:</strong> Mexico vs. South Korea – 9 p.m. (Guadalajara)</li>
          <li><strong>June 24:</strong> Playoff Winner vs. Mexico – 9 p.m. (Mexico City)</li>
          <li><strong>June 24:</strong> South Africa vs. South Korea – 9 p.m. (Monterrey)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-4">Group B</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li><strong>June 12:</strong> Canada vs. Playoff Winner – 3 p.m. (Toronto)</li>
          <li><strong>June 13:</strong> Qatar vs. Switzerland – 3 p.m. (San Francisco)</li>
          <li><strong>June 18:</strong> Switzerland vs. Playoff Winner – 3 p.m. (Los Angeles)</li>
          <li><strong>June 18:</strong> Canada vs. Qatar – 6 p.m. (Vancouver)</li>
          <li><strong>June 24:</strong> Switzerland vs. Canada – 3 p.m. (Vancouver)</li>
          <li><strong>June 24:</strong> Playoff Winner vs. Qatar – 3 p.m. (Seattle)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-4">Group C</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li><strong>June 13:</strong> Brazil vs. Morocco – 6 p.m. (NY/NJ)</li>
          <li><strong>June 13:</strong> Haiti vs. Scotland – 9 p.m. (Boston)</li>
          <li><strong>June 19:</strong> Scotland vs. Morocco – 6 p.m. (Boston)</li>
          <li><strong>June 19:</strong> Brazil vs. Haiti – 9 p.m. (Philadelphia)</li>
          <li><strong>June 24:</strong> Scotland vs. Brazil – 6 p.m. (Miami)</li>
          <li><strong>June 24:</strong> Morocco vs. Haiti – 6 p.m. (Atlanta)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-4">Group D</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li><strong>June 12:</strong> USA vs. Paraguay – 9 p.m. (Los Angeles)</li>
          <li><strong>June 13:</strong> Australia vs. Playoff Winner – 12 a.m. (Vancouver)</li>
          <li><strong>June 19:</strong> Playoff Winner vs. Paraguay – 12 a.m. (San Francisco)</li>
          <li><strong>June 19:</strong> USA vs. Australia – 3 p.m. (Seattle)</li>
          <li><strong>June 25:</strong> Playoff Winner vs. USA – 10 p.m. (Los Angeles)</li>
          <li><strong>June 25:</strong> Paraguay vs. Australia – 10 p.m. (San Francisco)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="my-10 p-6 bg-blue-900 text-white rounded-2xl shadow-inner">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Logistics and Tournament Structure</h2>
      <p class="text-blue-100">
        The 2026 World Cup will be the first to feature 104 matches and 48 participating teams. This <strong>fifa world cup 2026 fixture</strong> ensures a rest period of at least three days between almost every match, optimizing team recovery and fan travel logistics across the three host nations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-6">The Knockout Phase: Road to the Final</h2>
    <p>
      The <strong>fifa world cup 2026 fixture</strong> introduces the new Round of 32. The top two teams from each of the 12 groups, plus the eight best third-place finishers, will advance to this stage.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4 italic">Round of 32 Highlights</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Match 73:</strong> Runner-up Group A vs. Runner-up Group B – June 28 (Los Angeles)</li>
      <li><strong>Match 79:</strong> Winner Group A vs. 3rd Place C/E/F/H/I – June 30 (Mexico City)</li>
      <li><strong>Match 86:</strong> Winner Group J vs. Runner-up Group H – July 3 (Miami)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4 italic">Final Rounds</h3>
    <p>
      The <strong>fifa world cup 2026 fixture</strong> culminates in the biggest matches in sporting history:
    </p>
    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        <li><strong>Quarter-finals:</strong> Scheduled from July 9 to July 11 in Boston, LA, Miami, and Kansas City.</li>
        <li><strong>Semi-finals:</strong> July 14 (Dallas) and July 15 (Atlanta).</li>
        <li><strong>Third Place:</strong> July 18 (Miami).</li>
        <li><strong>Grand Final:</strong> July 19, MetLife Stadium, New York/New Jersey.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Participating Teams and Qualification</h2>
    <p>
      To date, 18 teams have confirmed their presence in the <strong>fifa world cup 2026 fixture</strong>: Argentina, Australia, Brazil, Canada, Colombia, South Korea, Ecuador, USA, Iran, Japan, Jordan, Morocco, Mexico, New Zealand, Paraguay, Tunisia, Uruguay, and Uzbekistan. The remaining spots will be decided in the March 2027 playoffs.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>